      {
        "id": 3195606,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2021-07-11T22:02:36.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>These wines age well, and quite slowly. To my palate, a vintage such as 2008 is perfect to drink right now. I think 2018 will likely evolve faster than 2008, but I would expect it to be better in five years than it is today, with no deterioration by any metric. I have quite a bit of 2017 and plan on attacking those in 2027 or so.</p>",
